03/10/2004
BRIJUNI, Croatia -- The army chiefs of the three Adriatic Charter signatories -- Albania's Pellumb Qazimi, Croatia's Josip Lukic and Macedonia's Gjorgi Bojadziev -- held talks Friday (1 October) in Brijoni, Croatia. They reaffirmed their determination to continue co-operation and work for faster integration into NATO. The talks were also attended by representatives of Bosnia and Herzegovina, Serbia-Montenegro, Italy, Hungary and Slovenia. (Utrinski Vesnik - 02/10/04; A1 TV, Hina, HIC - 01/10/04) 
